    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#CIG"/> <citedRange>5165</citedRange></bibl>, from 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#pacho1827"/>, pl. <citedRange>65, 6</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#vattier1850"/>, p. <citedRange>586</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>008000</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65298"><name nymRef="#Πεισίστρατος">Πεισίστρατος</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65078"><name nymRef="#Μυσός" type="patronymic">Μυσοῦ</name></persName></persName>	 
                </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Peisitratos fils de Mysos.</p> 
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Peisitratos son of Mysos.</p> 
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Peisitratos figlio di Mysos.</p> 
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>بيريستراتوس بن ميسوس</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
             <p>From the lettering and display on Pacho's copy, it appears that the stele (possibly a slab shuting a loculus) was first used on this side. Vattier de Bourville first copied also the inscriptions on the opposite side, which are clearly related to a re-use  
                 of later date and are thus duly published as <ref type="inscription" target="https://ircyr2020.inslib.kcl.ac.uk/en/inscriptions/C.562.html">IRCyr2020 C.562</ref>. The latter's copy being known only in print without any description of 
                 the lettering, the main side was erroneously republished as <ref type="inscription" target="https://ircyr2020.inslib.kcl.ac.uk/en/inscriptions/C.563.html">IRCyr2020 C.563</ref> and will be cancelled in a future edition.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
